// Onboarding Layout
// Shell for all onboarding pages. Provides OnboardingContext (mode, user, project, config),
// a full-width top header with project selector, search, and theme toggle,
// a sidebar with mode toggle and navigation below the header,
// and a main content area for child routes.
// synced: 2026-03-26T14:00:05Z

OnboardingContext carries: mode ('browse' | 'onboard'), currentUser, setMode, setUser, project, config.
Sidebar nav items: Browse, Graph, Dashboard (onboard only), Team (onboard only).

FUNCTION useOnboarding() -> OnboardingContextValue                      EXPORT
  Return the OnboardingContext value. Used by child pages to access mode, user, and project.

---

FUNCTION OnboardingLayout()                                             EXPORT  [2026-03-26]
  CALLS: fetchProjects (kodexStore), getConfig (onboarding-api)
  On mount: fetch registered projects.
  When selectedProject changes: fetch onboarding config via onboardingApi.getConfig.

  handleRefresh: re-fetch projects and config.

  handleModeToggle(newMode): update mode.
    IF switching to 'onboard' with no current user, navigate to /onboarding/welcome.
    IF switching to 'browse', navigate to /onboarding.

  handleSearch: on form submit, navigate to /onboarding/search?q=<query>.

  isActive(path): return true if location.pathname matches the nav item path.

  Render:
    - OnboardingContext.Provider wrapping the full layout.
    - Full-width top header (h-12) with: "Onboarding" route name label, refresh button,
      ProjectSelector, search input (when project selected), and theme toggle button.
    - Body row below the header:
      - Left sidebar with: mode toggle (Browse/Onboard, shown when project selected),
        nav links filtered by mode, user chip (onboard mode only), and cross-links to
        Kodex, Pseudo, and Collab. No own title — title is in the top header.
      - Main content: Outlet if project selected, else a "no project selected" placeholder.
